Equipment
Necromancers do not rely on physical defenses that can
disrupt or interfere their magical abilities.  As such, they are
restricted in the weapons and armour available to them.
Necromancers may not use medium, large, or huge weapons that are
of the pierce, cleave, or slash types.  Additionally, they may not
use any plate armour, or shields.  As a general rule, they may use
padded cloth armour, rings, and amulets.  They may also use
leather armour, but only for boots, gloves, and cloaks. Any
scale, banded, studded, chain, or padded armour that consists of
metal, leather, rock, or wood material will restrict the
Necromancer's abilities.
